### 2B-01: DataSourceAdapter Core + Auth

**PROMPT:**

```
Create the DataSourceAdapter core with authentication.

Create: src/server/datasource/DataSourceAdapter.ts

This is the main class that orchestrates all Yao API interactions.
It is instantiated once per pull with a firmId and handles all API communication.

class DataSourceAdapter {
  private firmId: string;
  private token: string | null = null;
  private baseUrl: string;  // from YAO_API_BASE_URL env var

  constructor(firmId: string)

  async authenticate(): Promise<void>
    - Calls credentialService.getCredentials(this.firmId)
    - POST {baseUrl}/attorneys/login with { email, password }
    - Response contains JWT token — search for it in: access_token, token, jwt,
      accessToken, authToken, or any key containing 'token' (case-insensitive)
    - Stores token in this.token
    - Throws YaoAuthError if login fails or token not found in response
    - Never logs credentials or token value

  private async request<T>(
    method: 'GET' | 'POST',
    path: string,
    options?: { params?: Record<string, string>; body?: object }
  ): Promise<T>
    - Throws if this.token is null (must call authenticate() first)
    - Adds Authorization: Bearer {token} header
    - Handles 401: throws YaoAuthExpiredError (token expired mid-pull)
    - Handles 429: waits 2 seconds and retries once
    - Handles 5xx: throws YaoApiError with status code and message
    - Parses JSON response, returns typed T

  async paginateGet<T>(
    path: string,
    params: Record<string, string>,
    resultKey: string,
    limit: number = 100
  ): Promise<T[]>
    - Loops GET requests incrementing page param
    - Stops when result array length < limit
    - resultKey is the response field containing the array (e.g. 'rows', 'items')
    - Returns all collected records

  async paginatePost<T>(
    path: string,
    body: object,
    resultKey: string,
    pageKey: 'page' | 'next',
    size: number = 100
  ): Promise<T[]>
    - For pageKey='page': loops incrementing page, stops when result < size
    - For pageKey='next': cursor pagination — sends next value from previous response,
      stops when next is absent/null in response
    - resultKey is the response field containing the array (e.g. 'result')
    - Returns all collected records
}

Create custom errors: src/server/datasource/errors.ts
  - YaoAuthError (login failed)
  - YaoAuthExpiredError (token expired mid-pull)
  - YaoApiError (HTTP error from API)
  - YaoRateLimitError (429 after retry)

Create: src/server/datasource/index.ts
  - Exports DataSourceAdapter and all error types

Write tests: tests/server/datasource/DataSourceAdapter.test.ts
  - authenticate() extracts token from various response shapes
  - request() adds correct Authorization header
  - paginateGet() stops correctly when result < limit
  - paginatePost() with cursor stops when next is absent
  - 429 retry logic works
  - authenticate() never logs credentials (spy on console methods)

Run tsc --noEmit ; commit "feat: DataSourceAdapter core with auth and pagination" ; push
```

